post_text: We want to stay strong & healthy! As we continue to promote the Health and Safety of all our students and staff in our District. Cloth face coverings will be required in our buildings anytime 6 foot social distancing cannot occur. We encourage you to find a cloth face mask that your child is comfortable with. We realize that students will need to have a variety of cloth face coverings to meet this expectation. One face mask will be offered to each student at the beginning of school year. It takes all of us to have a strong & healthy team! Please help us in making this a successful year: Go Spartans!

Information for those of you traveling to Ogden for Regional Softball Tomorrow night:
Covid-Related Information at Ogden:
* No bleachers. Fans are encouraged to bring a lawn chair.
* Masks are not required, but are encouraged.
* Dugouts will be sprayed down and sanitized before the game.
* No programs. Fans are encouraged to download the Varsity Bound app
* No concessions. Fans are permitted to bring their own coolers. Coolers may be searched upon request.
* Defensive team will be required to retrieve foul balls.

Admission: $6 adults/students. IHSAA passes only. Exact change preferred.
Gates Open: 6:00, Game Time: 7:00
Dugout Assignment: 1st base -- Ogden / 3rd base - Grundy Center

Due to the weather forecast for Saturday, "78 degrees with an 80% chance of showers and storms" we will be moving graduation indoors into the High School Gymnasium; set-up will require 24 hours as it includes stage, chairs, sound, video and broadcast. Please check your school email for information regarding changes to graduation. Please let me know if you have any questions or concerns. See you Saturday!

Mr. Vokes

Last week you received a letter from Superintendent Hughes giving you a brief explanation of the process we are following to develop a Return to Learn Plan for the 2020-2021 school year. The Grundy Center Community Schools Local Needs Assessment Survey and State Technology Access Survey are now live and available for you to complete. Please complete these surveys by Monday, June 22 so that your input can be considered as we plan for our Return to Learn this fall. All students grades 3-12, at least one parent, and all teachers and staff please take this survey! Your input is critical in helping us plan.

* The State Technology Access Survey is embedded in our Local Needs Assessment Survey. Scan the QR Code below to get started now!

Kindergarten/TK Round Up and TK Application Process

Grundy Center Elementary and GCP&CC Staff have worked to reschedule TK/Kindergarten Round Up due to CoVid-19 restrictions.

The new dates for Round Up are July 24 OR August 3 from 8:30am-10:30am with parent meetings running from 8:35am-8:50am on each of those days. We encourage attendance, but it is not mandatory.

There are 2 ways to complete Round Up registration.

1. Online at http://tiny.cc/aiqpnz by May 8, 2020.

2. Download the forms at http://tiny.cc/umqpnz and return them to Grundy Center Elementary by May 8, 2020.

Transitional Kindergarten selection will occur shortly after May 8, 2020.

Thank you for your patience. We are hopeful the new dates will still be an option as the summer progresses.

post_text:
SCHOOLS CLOSED FOR REMAINDER OF SCHOOL YEAR
Continuous Learning will be further implemented as Grundy Center Schools will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year per recommendation from Governor Reynolds on 4/17/20. Your child's continuous learning plan is in place and will continue. All spring sports are cancelled. School buildings will remain closed.

Our highest goals are to keep students, staff, and community safe; to offer assistance in class completion and graduation; and to support our students and families. Please encourage your student to participate in the continuous learning activities provided by teachers. If you have barriers to participate with these learning opportunities, please reach out to us via email. Stay safe, Spartans!

Please watch for further details related to educational expectations and engaging learning opportunities at www.spartanpride.net

Stay safe, Spartans!

-Mr. Hughes

Parents -
For those of you that are utilizing our Grab-n-Go meals from Grundy Center School- please read the following:

Due to newly-released USDA guidance, caregivers may pick up meals for children at Grab & Go meal sites, effective immediately. USDA recognizes that in this public health emergency, continuing to require children to come to the meal site to pick up meals may not be practical and in keeping with the goal of providing meals while also taking appropriate safety measures.

Either parents or students can pick up the meals. Grundy Center School will begin using this guideline on Monday at our 11:00 meal pick up at Bethany Presbyterian Church pickup.

post_text: Fall 2019 is one for the books! While we did not win the State Championship today the boys played with heart! Proud of Coach Zajac and staff for their remarkable season! State Cross Country for the boys,10th place overall, Taylor for the girls 28th overall. Volleyball team back to the Cell finishing at State. NICL Conference Band and Band Concert this week...don't forget your pies tomorrow! Robotics at home, Beauty and the Beast Musical this weekend and don't forget Girls Basketball on Tuesday...what?!? :) Our Staff, our students and our community...unbelievable! Spartan Pride runs deep! With all that success, with all that sacrifice, with all that effort, this might be what is at the center of it all...Spartan Pride! It is not a win/loss column, it's not a win at all cost mentality. It is the love we have for each other, the love we have for this community; this school! Capturing Hearts one student, one teacher, one person, at a time. I think the drum line captures it all! Watch it all the way through! Great Job Spartan Nation! Proud to be a Spartan!

post_text:
COMMUNITY LEADERS NEEDED!

Grundy Center Elementary is inviting leaders in our community to come to the elementary on Wednesday, September 11 from 2:30-3:00 to celebrate our Leader in Me Kickoff!

We ask that you be present to stand by and be examples of what good leadership looks like. Your visible support is all we need! As a bonus, you'll get to see what The Leader in Me is all about!

Business owners, librarians, emergency workers, doctors and nurses, bus drivers, police officers, courthouse workers, city workers, Chamber of Commerce, military and veterans, School Board.... ANYONE who displays leadership in what they do!

Please contact the elementary office if you plan to attend! 319.825.5461

Thank you!
